HERBARIUM OF THE UNIVERSITY OF MICHIGAN
*Galax aphylla* L.

DADE CO.: Summit of Lookout Mountain; near Little River
about 1.5 miles east of west brow, above Sulphur Springs
Station; pine-oak-hickory woodlands, in sandy soil; elev.
about 600 meters.

Abundant along bluffs of river;
leaves glossy-green; flowers white;
roots reddish.
